	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				In North Freeport, the woman behind the counter in Grohflah's forge sells clay.  There is a vendor in the first inn in East Commonlands that sells firing sheets.  A woman in the building to the right of the bank (as you face it) sells sketches.<BR>
<BR>
I have searched for a &quot;mixing bowl sketch&quot; with several characters.  I've surely annonyed a legion of players with my constant /shouts for information on where to find a mixing bowl sketch.  I've petitioned repeatedly and have yet to find a guide or GM who knows where the &quot;mixing bowl sketch&quot; is to be found.  I don't think there is one in the game.<BR>
<BR>
However, the Peacekeepers of Norrath (Tallon Zek server) have published a pottery guide that says the proper recipe for a mixing bowl is:<BR>
2 large blocks of clay<BR>
large bowl sketch<BR>
flask of water<BR>
(fire with firing sheet)<BR>
<BR>
This differs from the official Verant recipe, which calls for the apparently-mythical &quot;mixing bowl sketch.&quot;  I intend to try the Peacekeeper recipe this evening.<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
